Tiaty MP Asman Kamama yesterday said his rivals planned the attacks on him at the Churo and Tangulebei areas in his constituency on Saturday.Speaking to the Star on the phone, Kamama said he knows nothing of the killings of Loyamorok Ward MCA Kibet Cheretei and Tiaty MP aspirant Pepe Kitambaa. They were slain on Saturday last week.&ldquo;I am Innocent. It is my political enemies who want me to suffer for something I don&rsquo;t know about,&rdquo; Kamama said. He urged the public to ingnore &lsquo;rumours&rsquo; linking him to violence.He said the national government is doing everything possible to arrest those behind the killings of the two politicians.&ldquo;I am therefore urging warring communities to stop the bloodshed,&rdquo; Kamama said.He urged his Pokot tribesmen, who are grazing their cattle in the border areas of Baringo North and South, to go back home for the sake of peace and tranquility.&ldquo;You have been accused ofattacking your neighbours, who helped you with pastures. You now need to go back now as the government has ordered,&rdquo; Kamama said.He chairs the National Assembly Security committee .